The paper deals with the problem of detecting small obstacles on the road using stereo vision, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The proposed algorithm uses statistical hypothesis tests, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.AI) and statistical learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates the proposed method using a novel dataset, which could fall under the category of computer vision datasets (cs.CR).
